{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845984394,"sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ab36ae001RW0mFvw1dT0iYn","messageID":"msg_d78ab2bbb001Xw6XMR2hE3gDfV","sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n2: \n3: This proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: # AR-003 вҖ” CRD Shared Types and Constants\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: Extract and consolidate shared types, constants, and common structures used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs into a dedicated `shared_types.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`. This work eliminates code duplication, ensures consistency across CRD types, and establishes a single source of truth for common API primitives like network protocols, port definitions, and sandbox templates.\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In scope\n16: \n17: | Item | Detail |\n18: |------|--------|\n19: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n20: | **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (existing) |\n21: | **Version** | `v1alpha1` (existing) |\n22: | **Types defined** | `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `ConditionType`, `CommonCondition` |\n23: | **Constants defined** | Protocol constants (`ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`), Phase constants, Common condition type constants |\n24: | **Kubebuilder markers** | `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, validation markers (`+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`, `+kubebuilder:default`, etc.) |\n25: | **Code generation** | `controller-gen object` вҶ’ updates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` with shared types |\n26: \n27: ### Out of scope\n28: \n29: - Changes to `AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter` specific types (those remain in their respective files)\n30: - New CRD definitions\n31: - Workload Manager HTTP API changes\n32: - Controller/reconciler logic changes\n33: - Helm chart modifications\n34: - client-go generation (consumes types, doesn't define them)\n35: \n36: ## Design\n37: \n38: ### File layout\n39: \n40: | File | Role |\n41: |------|------|\n42: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | **NEW** вҖ” Shared types, constants, and common structures |\n43: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | **GENERATED** вҖ” DeepCopy methods for shared types (appended) |\n44: \n45: ### Type definitions\n46: \n47: **`ProtocolType`** вҖ” Shared protocol enumeration:\n48: \n49: ```go\n50: // ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n51: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;TCP;UDP\n52: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n53: type ProtocolType string\n54: \n55: const (\n56:     // ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n57:     ProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n58: \n59:     // ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n60:     ProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n61: \n62:     // ProtocolTCP represents the raw TCP protocol.\n63:     ProtocolTCP ProtocolType = \"TCP\"\n64: \n65:     // ProtocolUDP represents the UDP protocol.\n66:     ProtocolUDP ProtocolType = \"UDP\"\n67: )\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **`TargetPort`** вҖ” Shared port definition structure:\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: // TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n74: // This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\n75: type TargetPort struct {\n76:     // PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n77:     // Used primarily for HTTP/HTTPS protocols.\n78:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n79:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n80: \n81:     // Name is an optional name for this port.\n82:     // If specified, this name can be used to reference the port.\n83:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n84:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern=`^[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?$`\n85:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n86: \n87:     // Port is the port number to expose.\n88:     // This field is required.\n89:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n90:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n91:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n92:     Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n93: \n94:     // Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n95:     // Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n96:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n97:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n98:     Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n99: \n100:     // TargetPort is the port to access on the pods targeted by the service.\n101:     // Defaults to the Port value if not specified.\n102:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n103:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n104:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n105:     TargetPort int32 `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n106: }\n107: ```\n108: \n109: **`SandboxTemplate`** вҖ” Shared sandbox template structure:\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: // SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a sandbox.\n113: // It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n114: // This template is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to define\n115: // the underlying sandbox pod configuration.\n116: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n117:     // Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n118:     // These labels will be merged with any system-generated labels.\n119:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n120:     // +mapType=atomic\n121:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n122: \n123:     // Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n124:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n125:     // +mapType=atomic\n126:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n127: \n128:     // Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n129:     // This field is required and defines the container(s) to run.\n130:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n131:     Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n132: }\n133: ```\n134: \n135: **`SandboxPhase`** вҖ” Shared lifecycle phase enumeration:\n136: \n137: ```go\n138: // SandboxPhase represents the current phase of a sandbox resource.\n139: // This is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to indicate lifecycle state.\n140: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Creating;Running;Terminating;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n141: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n142: type SandboxPhase string\n143: \n144: const (\n145:     // SandboxPhasePending indicates the sandbox is pending creation.\n146:     SandboxPhasePending SandboxPhase = \"Pending\"\n147: \n148:     // SandboxPhaseCreating indicates the sandbox is being created.\n149:     SandboxPhaseCreating SandboxPhase = \"Creating\"\n150: \n151:     // SandboxPhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n152:     SandboxPhaseRunning SandboxPhase = \"Running\"\n153: \n154:     // SandboxPhaseTerminating indicates the sandbox is being terminated.\n155:     SandboxPhaseTerminating SandboxPhase = \"Terminating\"\n156: \n157:     // SandboxPhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n158:     SandboxPhaseSucceeded SandboxPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n159: \n160:     // SandboxPhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n161:     SandboxPhaseFailed SandboxPhase = \"Failed\"\n162: \n163:     // SandboxPhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n164:     SandboxPhaseUnknown SandboxPhase = \"Unknown\"\n165: )\n166: ```\n167: \n168: **`ConditionType`** вҖ” Shared condition type constants:\n169: \n170: ```go\n171: // CommonConditionType represents condition types shared across sandbox resources.\n172: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;Initialized;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed;Terminating\n173: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n174: type CommonConditionType string\n175: \n176: const (\n177:     // CommonConditionReady indicates the resource is ready to accept requests.\n178:     CommonConditionReady CommonConditionType = \"Ready\"\n179: \n180:     // CommonConditionInitialized indicates the resource has been initialized.\n181:     CommonConditionInitialized CommonConditionType = \"Initialized\"\n182: \n183:     // CommonConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n184:     CommonConditionSandboxCreated CommonConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n185: \n186:     // CommonConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n187:     CommonConditionSandboxReady CommonConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n188: \n189:     // CommonConditionFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n190:     CommonConditionFailed CommonConditionType = \"Failed\"\n191: \n192:     // CommonConditionTerminating indicates the resource is being terminated.\n193:     CommonConditionTerminating CommonConditionType = \"Terminating\"\n194: )\n195: ```\n196: \n197: **`CommonCondition`** вҖ” Shared condition structure:\n198: \n199: ```go\n200: // CommonCondition represents a condition of a sandbox resource.\n201: // This structure is shared by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter for status reporting.\n202: type CommonCondition struct {\n203:     // Type is the type of the condition.\n204:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n205:     Type CommonConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n206: \n207:     // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n208:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n209:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n210:     Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n211: \n212:     // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n213:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n214:     LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n215: \n216:     // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n217:     // This is typically a CamelCase string.\n218:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n219:     Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n220: \n221:     // Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n222:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n223:     Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Import requirements\n228: \n229: The shared types file requires these imports:\n230: \n231: ```go\n232: import (\n233:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n234:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n235: )\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Code generation pipeline\n239: \n240: ```\n241: controller-gen object вҶ’ pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go (appends shared types)\n242: ```\n243: \n244: Invocation: `make generate` or `make gen-all`\n245: \n246: ### Refactoring impact on existing types\n247: \n248: After creating `shared_types.go`, the following refactorings will be applied:\n249: \n250: | File | Change |\n251: |------|--------|\n252: | `codeinterpreter_types.go` | Remove `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`, `TargetPort`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (use shared types instead) |\n253: | `agentruntime_types.go` | Optionally adopt `TargetPort` and `SandboxTemplate` for consistency |\n254: \n255: **Note**: The actual refactoring of existing files is outside the scope of this AR; this AR only creates the shared types file. Subsequent ARs will handle the refactoring.\n256: \n257: ## Impact analysis\n258: \n259: ### Files created\n260: \n261: | File | Lines (est.) |\n262: |------|-------------|\n263: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~180 |\n264: \n265: ### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n266: \n267: | File | Tool |\n268: |------|------|\n269: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (appended) | `controller-gen object` |\n270: \n271: ### Downstream consumers\n272: \n273: | Consumer | Dependency |\n274: |----------|-----------|\n275: | `AgentRuntime` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` |\n276: | `CodeInterpreter` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` (replacing current definitions) |\n277: | `client-go` typed client | Will have DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n278: | Controllers | Can use shared condition types and phase constants |\n279: \n280: ### Breaking change risk\n281: \n282: - **None**: This is a new file with no changes to existing APIs.\n283: - **Future**: When existing types are refactored to use shared types, that will be a breaking change managed in separate ARs.\n284: - **Compatibility**: All shared types are additive and do not modify existing field names or structures.\n285: \n286: ## Alternatives considered\n287: \n288: ### 1. Keep types duplicated in each CRD file\n289: \n290: **Approach**: Maintain separate `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, etc. in both `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go`.\n291: \n292: **Rejected because**: Code duplication leads to maintenance overhead and potential inconsistencies. Changes to port definitions would need to be made in multiple places. The current `codeinterpreter_types.go` already defines these, and `AgentRuntime` may need similar structures in the future.\n293: \n294: ### 2. Create a separate API group for shared types\n295: \n296: **Approach**: Create a new API group `shared.agentcube.volcano.sh` or `core.agentcube.volcano.sh` for shared types.\n297: \n298: **Rejected because**: Overkill for a small set of shared types. Having shared types in the same `v1alpha1` package simplifies imports and keeps the API surface cohesive. Separate API groups would require additional scheme registration and client generation complexity.\n299: \n300: ### 3. Use Kubernetes native types exclusively\n301: \n302: **Approach**: Use `corev1.Protocol` instead of defining `ProtocolType`, use `corev1.ContainerPort` instead of `TargetPort`.\n303: \n304: **Rejected because**: AgentCube needs domain-specific validation and defaults (e.g., defaulting to HTTP, supporting only HTTP/HTTPS for now). Native types are too broad and don't allow for custom kubebuilder validation markers specific to AgentCube's use case.\n305: \n306: ### 4. Embed shared types as inline structs\n307: \n308: **Approach**: Define shared structures as inline anonymous structs within each CRD spec.\n309: \n310: **Rejected because**: Prevents code reuse and makes it impossible to define common utility functions or methods that work with these types. Also complicates code generation for DeepCopy methods.\n311: \n312: ## Dependencies\n313: \n314: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n315: |------------|---------|---------|\n316: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec`, `corev1.ConditionStatus` |\n317: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.Time` |\n318: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | DeepCopy generation for shared types |\n319: \n320: ## Verification\n321: \n322: ```bash\n323: # Generate DeepCopy methods (includes shared types)\n324: make generate\n325: \n326: # Verify compilation\n327: go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n328: \n329: # Run tests\n330: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n331: \n332: # Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\n333: make gen-check\n334: \n335: # Verify shared types can be imported and used\n336: go vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ## References\n340: \n341: - [AR-001](#ar-001--crd-agentruntime-type-definition) вҖ” AgentRuntime CRD types\n342: - [AR-002](#ar-002--crd-codeinterpreter-type-definition) вҖ” CodeInterpreter CRD types\n343: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n344: - [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: *AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 348 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 вҖ” CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtract and consolidate shared types, constants, and common structures used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs into a dedicated `shared_types.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`. This work eliminates code duplication, ensures consistency across CRD types, and establishes a single source of truth for common API primitives like network protocols, port definitions, and sandbox templates.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (existing) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775845984363,"end":1775845984392}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845984397,"sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ab3ac40011rdGO6hfxBB4AX","messageID":"msg_d78ab2bbb001Xw6XMR2hE3gDfV","sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 Design: CRD Shared Types and Constants (client-go)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-003  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Small  \n9: \n10: Generate the Kubernetes client-go library for the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The generated client provides programmatic access to `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs, including typed clients, informers, and listers.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: The client-go library follows the standard Kubernetes code-generation pattern, providing a layered architecture for interacting with custom resources:\n19: \n20: ```\n21: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n22: в”Ӯ                           Consumer Applications                              в”Ӯ\n23: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\n24: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Controllers в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    CLI Tools  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Workload Mgr в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Test Mocks в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n25: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”