{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845990969,"sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ab5ace001QNYvREceG5lxRm","messageID":"msg_d78ab48d3001vKZ6XlnfojxSMA","sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube вҖ” OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python вүҘ3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   вҶ’ Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      вҶ” Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      вҶ’ WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         вҶ” Redis/Valkey\n33:         вҶ’ K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube вҖ” OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python вүҘ3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775845990956,"end":1775845990968}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845990981,"sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ab5e47001pUzb1Ly4duSNgh","messageID":"msg_d78ab48d3001vKZ6XlnfojxSMA","sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client вҖ” `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n76: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n77: ```\n78: \n79: (Empty вҖ” reserved for custom methods.)\n80: \n81: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n82: \n83: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` вҖ” test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n88: \n89: | File | Role |\n90: |------|------|\n91: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n92: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Informer factory\n97: \n98: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n102: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n103: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n104: \tShutdown()\n105: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n106: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n107: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n108: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Constructors / options**\n113: \n114: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n115: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n116: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n117: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n118: \n119: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n120: \n121: ```go\n122: type Interface interface {\n123: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n128: \n129: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` вҶ’ `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` вҶ’ `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` вҖ” in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` вҶ’ `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/client-go.md","time":{"start":1775845990960,"end":1775845990978}}}}
