{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846056274,"sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ab84ac001hCPwZpBphFSA8m","messageID":"msg_d78ab6272001FvFNAjv4Na8nn1","sessionID":"ses_28755048cffeyTqEgd9FAr2NBB","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_functions.edit:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","oldString":"*AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*","newString":"*AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n\n---\n\n# AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Sandbox Creation Processor in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter` requests. The processor transforms user workload definitions (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRDs) into actual Sandbox or SandboxClaim Kubernetes resources, waits for them to reach running state, resolves Pod IP and entry points, persists session information to the Store, and returns a response containing the sessionId.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **HTTP Endpoints** | `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter` |\n| **Request types** | `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace |\n| **Response types** | `CreateSandboxResponse` with SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints |\n| **Core functionality** | Request validation, template retrieval, Sandbox/SandboxClaim object building, CR creation via dynamic client, async waiting for running state, Pod IP resolution, Store persistence |\n| **Integration with** | client-go informers/listers (AR-003), SandboxReconciler, Store (Redis), dynamic client |\n| **Error handling** | Validation errors (400), Not found (404), Quota exceeded (403), Timeout (500), with proper rollback |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Authentication/authorization logic (handled by authMiddleware in AR-004)\n- HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n- SandboxReconciler implementation (external controller)\n- Store implementation details\n- Helm chart modifications\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Object builders: `buildSandboxObject`, `buildSandboxClaimObject`, `resolvePodIP`, `buildEntryPoints` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Main creation orchestration: `sandboxCreator.createSandbox` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce` for waiting running state |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, label/annotation keys |\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n**`CreateSandboxRequest`**:\n\n```go\n// CreateSandboxRequest represents a request to create a new sandbox.\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n}\n\n// Validate rules:\n// - Kind must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n// - Namespace is required\n// - Name is required\n```\n\n**`CreateSandboxResponse`**:\n\n```go\n// CreateSandboxResponse represents the response after successful creation.\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // URL path prefix\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n}\n```\n\n### Sandbox Creation Flow\n\n```\nClient POST /v1/agent-runtime\n  вҶ’ authMiddleware (optional)\n    вҶ’ handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n      1. Parse and validate CreateSandboxRequest\n      2. Get AgentRuntime from Informer cache\n      3. Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim object (workload_builder)\n      4. StoreSandbox placeholder record\n      5. WatchSandboxOnce register one-time watcher\n      6. Create CR via dynamic client\n      7. Wait for SandboxReconciler notification (max 2 min)\n      8. Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n      9. UpdateSandbox with full info\n      10. Return CreateSandboxResponse\n```\n\n### Sandbox Object Building\n\n**AgentRuntime path** (`buildSandboxObject`):\n\n- Sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}` (8 random lowercase letters)\n- APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n- Kind: `Sandbox`\n- Labels: `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`, `managed-by`\n- Annotations: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n- Spec: `podTemplate` from `runtime.Spec.Template`, `replicas: 1`, `lifecycle.shutdownTime`\n\n**CodeInterpreter path**:\n\n- If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create `SandboxClaim` instead of full Sandbox\n- If `AuthMode == picod`: Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Default ports: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if `spec.Ports` empty\n\n### Pod IP Resolution\n\n```go\nfunc resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n    // 1. Check sandbox annotation \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n    // 2. Try informer cache with podName\n    // 3. Fallback: list pods by label SandboxNameLabelKey\n    // 4. Select pod with OwnerReference to Sandbox\n    // 5. Return pod.Status.PodIP if running\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling and Rollback\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Rollback Action |\n|------------|-------------|-----------------|\n| JSON binding failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Validation failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Template missing | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Not Found | 404 | None (before store) |\n| Auth failure | 401 | None (before handler) |\n| Timeout (>2 min) | 500 | Delete CR (30s timeout), Delete Store record |\n| Pod IP resolution failure | 500 | Delete CR, Delete Store record |\n| Store update failure | 500 | Log warning, CR cleaned by GC |\n\n### Timeout Configuration\n\n| Operation | Timeout |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Wait for Sandbox running | 2 minutes |\n| CR deletion on rollback | 30 seconds |\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | ~200 | Modified/Extended |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | ~300 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | ~250 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | ~150 | Modified/Extended |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ~50 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| WorkloadManager HTTP server | Uses handlers for sandbox endpoints |\n| client-go (AR-003) | Uses informers/listers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter lookup |\n| Store | Persists sandbox session information |\n| SandboxReconciler | Provides channel notification for running state |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n- **Future**: Changes to request/response schema may impact clients\n- **Compatibility**: Follows existing patterns from AR-004 HTTP framework\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Synchronous creation with long polling\n\n**Approach**: Block the HTTP request until Sandbox reaches running state.\n\n**Rejected because**: Synchronous creation would hold HTTP connections for up to 2 minutes, consuming server resources and potentially causing client timeouts. The async approach with Store placeholder allows immediate response with sessionId while background processing completes.\n\n### 2. Use typed client instead of dynamic client for Sandbox CRD\n\n**Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs.\n\n**Rejected because**: Sandbox and SandboxClaim are external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`, not part of agentcube's API. Using `dynamic.Interface` + `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for operating on CRDs with unknown schemas, avoiding dependency on external type definitions.\n\n### 3. Store session state in-memory only\n\n**Approach**: Keep sandbox session information only in memory.\n\n**Rejected because**: In-memory state would be lost on WorkloadManager restart. Using Redis/Store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling of WorkloadManager instances. Store also enables idempotency checks across instances.\n\n### 4. Watch for Sandbox status after CR creation\n\n**Approach**: Create CR first, then register watcher.\n\n**Rejected because**: Race condition - Sandbox could reach running state before watcher registration completes, causing indefinite wait. The correct order is: register watcher first, then create CR.\n\n### 5. Sequential integer sandbox IDs\n\n**Approach**: Use sequential integers (1, 2, 3...) for sandbox IDs instead of UUIDs.\n\n**Rejected because**: Sequential IDs require global coordination in distributed systems, creating a bottleneck. UUIDs provide global uniqueness without coordination, and align with Kubernetes naming conventions.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | v0.34.1 | Dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | UUID generation for sessionId |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | External | Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD definitions |\n| Store (Redis/Valkey) | - | Session persistence |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Integration tests with fake clientset\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run \"TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Verify handlers registered\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/v1/agent-runtime \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}'\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-003](#ar-003--crd-shared-types-and-constants) вҖ” client-go library for typed CRD access\n- [AR-004](#ar-004--http-service-framework) вҖ” HTTP server framework and routing\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Generated client details\n- [sandbox-orchestration design](sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md) вҖ” Detailed technical design\n- [Kubernetes Dynamic Client](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/dynamic) вҖ” For external CRD operations\n\n---\n\n*AR-005 вҖ” Module: pkg/workloadmanager вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n@@ -345,4 +345,251 @@\n \n ---\n \n *AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n+\n+---\n+\n+# AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox Creation Processor\n+\n+## Purpose\n+\n+Implement the Sandbox Creation Processor in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter` requests. The processor transforms user workload definitions (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRDs) into actual Sandbox or SandboxClaim Kubernetes resources, waits for them to reach running state, resolves Pod IP and entry points, persists session information to the Store, and returns a response containing the sessionId.\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+### In scope\n+\n+| Item | Detail |\n+|------|--------|\n+| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n+| **HTTP Endpoints** | `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter` |\n+| **Request types** | `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace |\n+| **Response types** | `CreateSandboxResponse` with SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints |\n+| **Core functionality** | Request validation, template retrieval, Sandbox/SandboxClaim object building, CR creation via dynamic client, async waiting for running state, Pod IP resolution, Store persistence |\n+| **Integration with** | client-go informers/listers (AR-003), SandboxReconciler, Store (Redis), dynamic client |\n+| **Error handling** | Validation errors (400), Not found (404), Quota exceeded (403), Timeout (500), with proper rollback |\n+\n+### Out of scope\n+\n+- Authentication/authorization logic (handled by authMiddleware in AR-004)\n+- HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n+- SandboxReconciler implementation (external controller)\n+- Store implementation details\n+- Helm chart modifications\n+\n+## Design\n+\n+### File layout\n+\n+| File | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Object builders: `buildSandboxObject`, `buildSandboxClaimObject`, `resolvePodIP`, `buildEntryPoints` |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Main creation orchestration: `sandboxCreator.createSandbox` |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce` for waiting running state |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, label/annotation keys |\n+\n+### Request/Response Types\n+\n+**`CreateSandboxRequest`**:\n+\n+```go\n+// CreateSandboxRequest represents a request to create a new sandbox.\n+type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n+    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n+    Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n+    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n+}\n+\n+// Validate rules:\n+// - Kind must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n+// - Namespace is required\n+// - Name is required\n+```\n+\n+**`CreateSandboxResponse`**:\n+\n+```go\n+// CreateSandboxResponse represents the response after successful creation.\n+type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n+    SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n+    SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n+    SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n+    EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n+}\n+\n+type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n+    Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // URL path prefix\n+    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n+    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Sandbox Creation Flow\n+\n+```\n+Client POST /v1/agent-runtime\n+  вҶ’ authMiddleware (optional)\n+    вҶ’ handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n+      1. Parse and validate CreateSandboxRequest\n+      2. Get AgentRuntime from Informer cache\n+      3. Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim object (workload_builder)\n+      4. StoreSandbox placeholder record\n+      5. WatchSandboxOnce register one-time watcher\n+      6. Create CR via dynamic client\n+      7. Wait for SandboxReconciler notification (max 2 min)\n+      8. Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n+      9. UpdateSandbox with full info\n+      10. Return CreateSandboxResponse\n+```\n+\n+### Sandbox Object Building\n+\n+**AgentRuntime path** (`buildSandboxObject`):\n+\n+- Sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}` (8 random lowercase letters)\n+- APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n+- Kind: `Sandbox`\n+- Labels: `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`, `managed-by`\n+- Annotations: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n+- Spec: `podTemplate` from `runtime.Spec.Template`, `replicas: 1`, `lifecycle.shutdownTime`\n+\n+**CodeInterpreter path**:\n+\n+- If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create `SandboxClaim` instead of full Sandbox\n+- If `AuthMode == picod`: Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n+- Default ports: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if `spec.Ports` empty\n+\n+### Pod IP Resolution\n+\n+```go\n+func resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n+    // 1. Check sandbox annotation \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n+    // 2. Try informer cache with podName\n+    // 3. Fallback: list pods by label SandboxNameLabelKey\n+    // 4. Select pod with OwnerReference to Sandbox\n+    // 5. Return pod.Status.PodIP if running\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Error Handling and Rollback\n+\n+| Error Type | HTTP Status | Rollback Action |\n+|------------|-------------|-----------------|\n+| JSON binding failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n+| Validation failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n+| Template missing | 400 | None (before store) |\n+| Not Found | 404 | None (before store) |\n+| Auth failure | 401 | None (before handler) |\n+| Timeout (>2 min) | 500 | Delete CR (30s timeout), Delete Store record |\n+| Pod IP resolution failure | 500 | Delete CR, Delete Store record |\n+| Store update failure | 500 | Log warning, CR cleaned by GC |\n+\n+### Timeout Configuration\n+\n+| Operation | Timeout |\n+|-----------|---------|\n+| Wait for Sandbox running | 2 minutes |\n+| CR deletion on rollback | 30 seconds |\n+\n+## Impact Analysis\n+\n+### Files created/modified\n+\n+| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n+|------|-------------|------|\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | ~200 | Modified/Extended |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | ~300 | New |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | ~250 | New |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | ~150 | Modified/Extended |\n+| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ~50 | New |\n+\n+### Downstream consumers\n+\n+| Consumer | Dependency |\n+|----------|-----------|\n+| WorkloadManager HTTP server | Uses handlers for sandbox endpoints |\n+| client-go (AR-003) | Uses informers/listers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter lookup |\n+| Store | Persists sandbox session information |\n+| SandboxReconciler | Provides channel notification for running state |\n+\n+### Breaking change risk\n+\n+- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n+- **Future**: Changes to request/response schema may impact clients\n+- **Compatibility**: Follows existing patterns from AR-004 HTTP framework\n+\n+## Alternatives Considered\n+\n+### 1. Synchronous creation with long polling\n+\n+**Approach**: Block the HTTP request until Sandbox reaches running state.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Synchronous creation would hold HTTP connections for up to 2 minutes, consuming server resources and potentially causing client timeouts. The async approach with Store placeholder allows immediate response with sessionId while background processing completes.\n+\n+### 2. Use typed client instead of dynamic client for Sandbox CRD\n+\n+**Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Sandbox and SandboxClaim are external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`, not part of agentcube's API. Using `dynamic.Interface` + `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for operating on CRDs with unknown schemas, avoiding dependency on external type definitions.\n+\n+### 3. Store session state in-memory only\n+\n+**Approach**: Keep sandbox session information only in memory.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: In-memory state would be lost on WorkloadManager restart. Using Redis/Store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling of WorkloadManager instances. Store also enables idempotency checks across instances.\n+\n+### 4. Watch for Sandbox status after CR creation\n+\n+**Approach**: Create CR first, then register watcher.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Race condition - Sandbox could reach running state before watcher registration completes, causing indefinite wait. The correct order is: register watcher first, then create CR.\n+\n+### 5. Sequential integer sandbox IDs\n+\n+**Approach**: Use sequential integers (1, 2, 3...) for sandbox IDs instead of UUIDs.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Sequential IDs require global coordination in distributed systems, creating a bottleneck. UUIDs provide global uniqueness without coordination, and align with Kubernetes naming conventions.\n+\n+## Dependencies\n+\n+| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n+|------------|---------|---------|\n+| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n+| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | v0.34.1 | Dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs |\n+| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | UUID generation for sessionId |\n+| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | External | Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD definitions |\n+| Store (Redis/Valkey) | - | Session persistence |\n+\n+## Verification\n+\n+```bash\n+# Unit tests\n+make test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+\n+# Integration tests with fake clientset\n+go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run \"TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate\"\n+\n+# Build verification\n+go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+\n+# Verify handlers registered\n+curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/v1/agent-runtime \\\n+  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n+  -d '{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}'\n+\n+# Verify race conditions\n+go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+```\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- [AR-003](#ar-003--crd-shared-types-and-constants) вҖ” client-go library for typed CRD access\n+- [AR-004](#ar-004--http-service-framework) вҖ” HTTP server framework and routing\n+- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Generated client details\n+- [sandbox-orchestration design](sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md) вҖ” Detailed technical design\n+- [Kubernetes Dynamic Client](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/dynamic) вҖ” For external CRD operations\n+\n+---\n+\n+*AR-005 вҖ” Module: pkg/workloadmanager вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","before":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 вҖ” CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtract and consolidate shared types, constants, and common structures used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs into a dedicated `shared_types.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`. This work eliminates code duplication, ensures consistency across CRD types, and establishes a single source of truth for common API primitives like network protocols, port definitions, and sandbox templates.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (existing) |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` (existing) |\n| **Types defined** | `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `ConditionType`, `CommonCondition` |\n| **Constants defined** | Protocol constants (`ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`), Phase constants, Common condition type constants |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, validation markers (`+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`, `+kubebuilder:default`, etc.) |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen object` вҶ’ updates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` with shared types |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Changes to `AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter` specific types (those remain in their respective files)\n- New CRD definitions\n- Workload Manager HTTP API changes\n- Controller/reconciler logic changes\n- Helm chart modifications\n- client-go generation (consumes types, doesn't define them)\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | **NEW** вҖ” Shared types, constants, and common structures |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | **GENERATED** вҖ” DeepCopy methods for shared types (appended) |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`ProtocolType`** вҖ” Shared protocol enumeration:\n\n```go\n// ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;TCP;UDP\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n    // ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n\n    // ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n\n    // ProtocolTCP represents the raw TCP protocol.\n    ProtocolTCP ProtocolType = \"TCP\"\n\n    // ProtocolUDP represents the UDP protocol.\n    ProtocolUDP ProtocolType = \"UDP\"\n)\n```\n\n**`TargetPort`** вҖ” Shared port definition structure:\n\n```go\n// TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n// This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    // PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n    // Used primarily for HTTP/HTTPS protocols.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Name is an optional name for this port.\n    // If specified, this name can be used to reference the port.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern=`^[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?$`\n    Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Port is the port number to expose.\n    // This field is required.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n\n    // Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n    // Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n    Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TargetPort is the port to access on the pods targeted by the service.\n    // Defaults to the Port value if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    TargetPort int32 `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxTemplate`** вҖ” Shared sandbox template structure:\n\n```go\n// SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a sandbox.\n// It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n// This template is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to define\n// the underlying sandbox pod configuration.\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    // Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // These labels will be merged with any system-generated labels.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n    // This field is required and defines the container(s) to run.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxPhase`** вҖ” Shared lifecycle phase enumeration:\n\n```go\n// SandboxPhase represents the current phase of a sandbox resource.\n// This is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to indicate lifecycle state.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Creating;Running;Terminating;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype SandboxPhase string\n\nconst (\n    // SandboxPhasePending indicates the sandbox is pending creation.\n    SandboxPhasePending SandboxPhase = \"Pending\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseCreating indicates the sandbox is being created.\n    SandboxPhaseCreating SandboxPhase = \"Creating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n    SandboxPhaseRunning SandboxPhase = \"Running\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseTerminating indicates the sandbox is being terminated.\n    SandboxPhaseTerminating SandboxPhase = \"Terminating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n    SandboxPhaseSucceeded SandboxPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n    SandboxPhaseFailed SandboxPhase = \"Failed\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n    SandboxPhaseUnknown SandboxPhase = \"Unknown\"\n)\n```\n\n**`ConditionType`** вҖ” Shared condition type constants:\n\n```go\n// CommonConditionType represents condition types shared across sandbox resources.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;Initialized;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed;Terminating\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CommonConditionType string\n\nconst (\n    // CommonConditionReady indicates the resource is ready to accept requests.\n    CommonConditionReady CommonConditionType = \"Ready\"\n\n    // CommonConditionInitialized indicates the resource has been initialized.\n    CommonConditionInitialized CommonConditionType = \"Initialized\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n    CommonConditionSandboxCreated CommonConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n    CommonConditionSandboxReady CommonConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n\n    // CommonConditionFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n    CommonConditionFailed CommonConditionType = \"Failed\"\n\n    // CommonConditionTerminating indicates the resource is being terminated.\n    CommonConditionTerminating CommonConditionType = \"Terminating\"\n)\n```\n\n**`CommonCondition`** вҖ” Shared condition structure:\n\n```go\n// CommonCondition represents a condition of a sandbox resource.\n// This structure is shared by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter for status reporting.\ntype CommonCondition struct {\n    // Type is the type of the condition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Type CommonConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n    Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n\n    // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n    // This is typically a CamelCase string.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Import requirements\n\nThe shared types file requires these imports:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen object вҶ’ pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go (appends shared types)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make generate` or `make gen-all`\n\n### Refactoring impact on existing types\n\nAfter creating `shared_types.go`, the following refactorings will be applied:\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `codeinterpreter_types.go` | Remove `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`, `TargetPort`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (use shared types instead) |\n| `agentruntime_types.go` | Optionally adopt `TargetPort` and `SandboxTemplate` for consistency |\n\n**Note**: The actual refactoring of existing files is outside the scope of this AR; this AR only creates the shared types file. Subsequent ARs will handle the refactoring.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~180 |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (appended) | `controller-gen object` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `AgentRuntime` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` |\n| `CodeInterpreter` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` (replacing current definitions) |\n| `client-go` typed client | Will have DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n| Controllers | Can use shared condition types and phase constants |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None**: This is a new file with no changes to existing APIs.\n- **Future**: When existing types are refactored to use shared types, that will be a breaking change managed in separate ARs.\n- **Compatibility**: All shared types are additive and do not modify existing field names or structures.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Keep types duplicated in each CRD file\n\n**Approach**: Maintain separate `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, etc. in both `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go`.\n\n**Rejected because**: Code duplication leads to maintenance overhead and potential inconsistencies. Changes to port definitions would need to be made in multiple places. The current `codeinterpreter_types.go` already defines these, and `AgentRuntime` may need similar structures in the future.\n\n### 2. Create a separate API group for shared types\n\n**Approach**: Create a new API group `shared.agentcube.volcano.sh` or `core.agentcube.volcano.sh` for shared types.\n\n**Rejected because**: Overkill for a small set of shared types. Having shared types in the same `v1alpha1` package simplifies imports and keeps the API surface cohesive. Separate API groups would require additional scheme registration and client generation complexity.\n\n### 3. Use Kubernetes native types exclusively\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.Protocol` instead of defining `ProtocolType`, use `corev1.ContainerPort` instead of `TargetPort`.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube needs domain-specific validation and defaults (e.g., defaulting to HTTP, supporting only HTTP/HTTPS for now). Native types are too broad and don't allow for custom kubebuilder validation markers specific to AgentCube's use case.\n\n### 4. Embed shared types as inline structs\n\n**Approach**: Define shared structures as inline anonymous structs within each CRD spec.\n\n**Rejected because**: Prevents code reuse and makes it impossible to define common utility functions or methods that work with these types. Also complicates code generation for DeepCopy methods.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec`, `corev1.ConditionStatus` |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.Time` |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | DeepCopy generation for shared types |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate DeepCopy methods (includes shared types)\nmake generate\n\n# Verify compilation\ngo build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Verify shared types can be imported and used\ngo vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-001](#ar-001--crd-agentruntime-type-definition) вҖ” AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [AR-002](#ar-002--crd-codeinterpreter-type-definition) вҖ” CodeInterpreter CRD types\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n---\n\n*AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n","after":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 вҖ” CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtract and consolidate shared types, constants, and common structures used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs into a dedicated `shared_types.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`. This work eliminates code duplication, ensures consistency across CRD types, and establishes a single source of truth for common API primitives like network protocols, port definitions, and sandbox templates.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (existing) |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` (existing) |\n| **Types defined** | `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `ConditionType`, `CommonCondition` |\n| **Constants defined** | Protocol constants (`ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`), Phase constants, Common condition type constants |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, validation markers (`+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`, `+kubebuilder:default`, etc.) |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen object` вҶ’ updates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` with shared types |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Changes to `AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter` specific types (those remain in their respective files)\n- New CRD definitions\n- Workload Manager HTTP API changes\n- Controller/reconciler logic changes\n- Helm chart modifications\n- client-go generation (consumes types, doesn't define them)\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | **NEW** вҖ” Shared types, constants, and common structures |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | **GENERATED** вҖ” DeepCopy methods for shared types (appended) |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`ProtocolType`** вҖ” Shared protocol enumeration:\n\n```go\n// ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;TCP;UDP\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n    // ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n\n    // ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n\n    // ProtocolTCP represents the raw TCP protocol.\n    ProtocolTCP ProtocolType = \"TCP\"\n\n    // ProtocolUDP represents the UDP protocol.\n    ProtocolUDP ProtocolType = \"UDP\"\n)\n```\n\n**`TargetPort`** вҖ” Shared port definition structure:\n\n```go\n// TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n// This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    // PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n    // Used primarily for HTTP/HTTPS protocols.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Name is an optional name for this port.\n    // If specified, this name can be used to reference the port.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern=`^[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?$`\n    Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Port is the port number to expose.\n    // This field is required.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n\n    // Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n    // Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n    Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TargetPort is the port to access on the pods targeted by the service.\n    // Defaults to the Port value if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    TargetPort int32 `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxTemplate`** вҖ” Shared sandbox template structure:\n\n```go\n// SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a sandbox.\n// It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n// This template is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to define\n// the underlying sandbox pod configuration.\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    // Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // These labels will be merged with any system-generated labels.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n    // This field is required and defines the container(s) to run.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxPhase`** вҖ” Shared lifecycle phase enumeration:\n\n```go\n// SandboxPhase represents the current phase of a sandbox resource.\n// This is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to indicate lifecycle state.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Creating;Running;Terminating;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype SandboxPhase string\n\nconst (\n    // SandboxPhasePending indicates the sandbox is pending creation.\n    SandboxPhasePending SandboxPhase = \"Pending\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseCreating indicates the sandbox is being created.\n    SandboxPhaseCreating SandboxPhase = \"Creating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n    SandboxPhaseRunning SandboxPhase = \"Running\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseTerminating indicates the sandbox is being terminated.\n    SandboxPhaseTerminating SandboxPhase = \"Terminating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n    SandboxPhaseSucceeded SandboxPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n    SandboxPhaseFailed SandboxPhase = \"Failed\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n    SandboxPhaseUnknown SandboxPhase = \"Unknown\"\n)\n```\n\n**`ConditionType`** вҖ” Shared condition type constants:\n\n```go\n// CommonConditionType represents condition types shared across sandbox resources.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;Initialized;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed;Terminating\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CommonConditionType string\n\nconst (\n    // CommonConditionReady indicates the resource is ready to accept requests.\n    CommonConditionReady CommonConditionType = \"Ready\"\n\n    // CommonConditionInitialized indicates the resource has been initialized.\n    CommonConditionInitialized CommonConditionType = \"Initialized\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n    CommonConditionSandboxCreated CommonConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n    CommonConditionSandboxReady CommonConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n\n    // CommonConditionFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n    CommonConditionFailed CommonConditionType = \"Failed\"\n\n    // CommonConditionTerminating indicates the resource is being terminated.\n    CommonConditionTerminating CommonConditionType = \"Terminating\"\n)\n```\n\n**`CommonCondition`** вҖ” Shared condition structure:\n\n```go\n// CommonCondition represents a condition of a sandbox resource.\n// This structure is shared by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter for status reporting.\ntype CommonCondition struct {\n    // Type is the type of the condition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Type CommonConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n    Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n\n    // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n    // This is typically a CamelCase string.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Import requirements\n\nThe shared types file requires these imports:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen object вҶ’ pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go (appends shared types)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make generate` or `make gen-all`\n\n### Refactoring impact on existing types\n\nAfter creating `shared_types.go`, the following refactorings will be applied:\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `codeinterpreter_types.go` | Remove `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`, `TargetPort`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (use shared types instead) |\n| `agentruntime_types.go` | Optionally adopt `TargetPort` and `SandboxTemplate` for consistency |\n\n**Note**: The actual refactoring of existing files is outside the scope of this AR; this AR only creates the shared types file. Subsequent ARs will handle the refactoring.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~180 |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (appended) | `controller-gen object` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `AgentRuntime` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` |\n| `CodeInterpreter` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` (replacing current definitions) |\n| `client-go` typed client | Will have DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n| Controllers | Can use shared condition types and phase constants |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None**: This is a new file with no changes to existing APIs.\n- **Future**: When existing types are refactored to use shared types, that will be a breaking change managed in separate ARs.\n- **Compatibility**: All shared types are additive and do not modify existing field names or structures.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Keep types duplicated in each CRD file\n\n**Approach**: Maintain separate `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, etc. in both `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go`.\n\n**Rejected because**: Code duplication leads to maintenance overhead and potential inconsistencies. Changes to port definitions would need to be made in multiple places. The current `codeinterpreter_types.go` already defines these, and `AgentRuntime` may need similar structures in the future.\n\n### 2. Create a separate API group for shared types\n\n**Approach**: Create a new API group `shared.agentcube.volcano.sh` or `core.agentcube.volcano.sh` for shared types.\n\n**Rejected because**: Overkill for a small set of shared types. Having shared types in the same `v1alpha1` package simplifies imports and keeps the API surface cohesive. Separate API groups would require additional scheme registration and client generation complexity.\n\n### 3. Use Kubernetes native types exclusively\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.Protocol` instead of defining `ProtocolType`, use `corev1.ContainerPort` instead of `TargetPort`.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube needs domain-specific validation and defaults (e.g., defaulting to HTTP, supporting only HTTP/HTTPS for now). Native types are too broad and don't allow for custom kubebuilder validation markers specific to AgentCube's use case.\n\n### 4. Embed shared types as inline structs\n\n**Approach**: Define shared structures as inline anonymous structs within each CRD spec.\n\n**Rejected because**: Prevents code reuse and makes it impossible to define common utility functions or methods that work with these types. Also complicates code generation for DeepCopy methods.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec`, `corev1.ConditionStatus` |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.Time` |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | DeepCopy generation for shared types |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate DeepCopy methods (includes shared types)\nmake generate\n\n# Verify compilation\ngo build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Verify shared types can be imported and used\ngo vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-001](#ar-001--crd-agentruntime-type-definition) вҖ” AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [AR-002](#ar-002--crd-codeinterpreter-type-definition) вҖ” CodeInterpreter CRD types\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n---\n\n*AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n\n---\n\n# AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Sandbox Creation Processor in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter` requests. The processor transforms user workload definitions (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRDs) into actual Sandbox or SandboxClaim Kubernetes resources, waits for them to reach running state, resolves Pod IP and entry points, persists session information to the Store, and returns a response containing the sessionId.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **HTTP Endpoints** | `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter` |\n| **Request types** | `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace |\n| **Response types** | `CreateSandboxResponse` with SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints |\n| **Core functionality** | Request validation, template retrieval, Sandbox/SandboxClaim object building, CR creation via dynamic client, async waiting for running state, Pod IP resolution, Store persistence |\n| **Integration with** | client-go informers/listers (AR-003), SandboxReconciler, Store (Redis), dynamic client |\n| **Error handling** | Validation errors (400), Not found (404), Quota exceeded (403), Timeout (500), with proper rollback |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Authentication/authorization logic (handled by authMiddleware in AR-004)\n- HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n- SandboxReconciler implementation (external controller)\n- Store implementation details\n- Helm chart modifications\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Object builders: `buildSandboxObject`, `buildSandboxClaimObject`, `resolvePodIP`, `buildEntryPoints` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Main creation orchestration: `sandboxCreator.createSandbox` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce` for waiting running state |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, label/annotation keys |\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n**`CreateSandboxRequest`**:\n\n```go\n// CreateSandboxRequest represents a request to create a new sandbox.\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n}\n\n// Validate rules:\n// - Kind must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n// - Namespace is required\n// - Name is required\n```\n\n**`CreateSandboxResponse`**:\n\n```go\n// CreateSandboxResponse represents the response after successful creation.\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // URL path prefix\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n}\n```\n\n### Sandbox Creation Flow\n\n```\nClient POST /v1/agent-runtime\n  вҶ’ authMiddleware (optional)\n    вҶ’ handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n      1. Parse and validate CreateSandboxRequest\n      2. Get AgentRuntime from Informer cache\n      3. Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim object (workload_builder)\n      4. StoreSandbox placeholder record\n      5. WatchSandboxOnce register one-time watcher\n      6. Create CR via dynamic client\n      7. Wait for SandboxReconciler notification (max 2 min)\n      8. Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n      9. UpdateSandbox with full info\n      10. Return CreateSandboxResponse\n```\n\n### Sandbox Object Building\n\n**AgentRuntime path** (`buildSandboxObject`):\n\n- Sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}` (8 random lowercase letters)\n- APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n- Kind: `Sandbox`\n- Labels: `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`, `managed-by`\n- Annotations: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n- Spec: `podTemplate` from `runtime.Spec.Template`, `replicas: 1`, `lifecycle.shutdownTime`\n\n**CodeInterpreter path**:\n\n- If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create `SandboxClaim` instead of full Sandbox\n- If `AuthMode == picod`: Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Default ports: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if `spec.Ports` empty\n\n### Pod IP Resolution\n\n```go\nfunc resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n    // 1. Check sandbox annotation \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n    // 2. Try informer cache with podName\n    // 3. Fallback: list pods by label SandboxNameLabelKey\n    // 4. Select pod with OwnerReference to Sandbox\n    // 5. Return pod.Status.PodIP if running\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling and Rollback\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Rollback Action |\n|------------|-------------|-----------------|\n| JSON binding failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Validation failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Template missing | 400 | None (before store) |\n| Not Found | 404 | None (before store) |\n| Auth failure | 401 | None (before handler) |\n| Timeout (>2 min) | 500 | Delete CR (30s timeout), Delete Store record |\n| Pod IP resolution failure | 500 | Delete CR, Delete Store record |\n| Store update failure | 500 | Log warning, CR cleaned by GC |\n\n### Timeout Configuration\n\n| Operation | Timeout |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Wait for Sandbox running | 2 minutes |\n| CR deletion on rollback | 30 seconds |\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | ~200 | Modified/Extended |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | ~300 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | ~250 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | ~150 | Modified/Extended |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ~50 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| WorkloadManager HTTP server | Uses handlers for sandbox endpoints |\n| client-go (AR-003) | Uses informers/listers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter lookup |\n| Store | Persists sandbox session information |\n| SandboxReconciler | Provides channel notification for running state |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n- **Future**: Changes to request/response schema may impact clients\n- **Compatibility**: Follows existing patterns from AR-004 HTTP framework\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Synchronous creation with long polling\n\n**Approach**: Block the HTTP request until Sandbox reaches running state.\n\n**Rejected because**: Synchronous creation would hold HTTP connections for up to 2 minutes, consuming server resources and potentially causing client timeouts. The async approach with Store placeholder allows immediate response with sessionId while background processing completes.\n\n### 2. Use typed client instead of dynamic client for Sandbox CRD\n\n**Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs.\n\n**Rejected because**: Sandbox and SandboxClaim are external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`, not part of agentcube's API. Using `dynamic.Interface` + `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for operating on CRDs with unknown schemas, avoiding dependency on external type definitions.\n\n### 3. Store session state in-memory only\n\n**Approach**: Keep sandbox session information only in memory.\n\n**Rejected because**: In-memory state would be lost on WorkloadManager restart. Using Redis/Store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling of WorkloadManager instances. Store also enables idempotency checks across instances.\n\n### 4. Watch for Sandbox status after CR creation\n\n**Approach**: Create CR first, then register watcher.\n\n**Rejected because**: Race condition - Sandbox could reach running state before watcher registration completes, causing indefinite wait. The correct order is: register watcher first, then create CR.\n\n### 5. Sequential integer sandbox IDs\n\n**Approach**: Use sequential integers (1, 2, 3...) for sandbox IDs instead of UUIDs.\n\n**Rejected because**: Sequential IDs require global coordination in distributed systems, creating a bottleneck. UUIDs provide global uniqueness without coordination, and align with Kubernetes naming conventions.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | v0.34.1 | Dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | UUID generation for sessionId |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | External | Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD definitions |\n| Store (Redis/Valkey) | - | Session persistence |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Integration tests with fake clientset\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run \"TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Verify handlers registered\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/v1/agent-runtime \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}'\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-003](#ar-003--crd-shared-types-and-constants) вҖ” client-go library for typed CRD access\n- [AR-004](#ar-004--http-service-framework) вҖ” HTTP server framework and routing\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Generated client details\n- [sandbox-orchestration design](sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md) вҖ” Detailed technical design\n- [Kubernetes Dynamic Client](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/dynamic) вҖ” For external CRD operations\n\n---\n\n*AR-005 вҖ” Module: pkg/workloadmanager вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*\n","additions":247,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775846056240,"end":1775846056269}}}}
