n361: \n362: | Item | Detail |\n363: |------|--------|\n364: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n365: | **HTTP Endpoints** | `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter` |\n366: | **Request types** | `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace |\n367: | **Response types** | `CreateSandboxResponse` with SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints |\n368: | **Core functionality** | Request validation, template retrieval, Sandbox/SandboxClaim object building, CR creation via dynamic client, async waiting for running state, Pod IP resolution, Store persistence |\n369: | **Integration with** | client-go informers/listers (AR-003), SandboxReconciler, Store (Redis), dynamic client |\n370: | **Error handling** | Validation errors (400), Not found (404), Quota exceeded (403), Timeout (500), with proper rollback |\n371: \n372: ### Out of scope\n373: \n374: - Authentication/authorization logic (handled by authMiddleware in AR-004)\n375: - HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n376: - SandboxReconciler implementation (external controller)\n377: - Store implementation details\n378: - Helm chart modifications\n379: \n380: ## Design\n381: \n382: ### File layout\n383: \n384: | File | Role |\n385: |------|------|\n386: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n387: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Object builders: `buildSandboxObject`, `buildSandboxClaimObject`, `resolvePodIP`, `buildEntryPoints` |\n388: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Main creation orchestration: `sandboxCreator.createSandbox` |\n389: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce` for waiting running state |\n390: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, label/annotation keys |\n391: \n392: ### Request/Response Types\n393: \n394: **`CreateSandboxRequest`**:\n395: \n396: ```go\n397: // CreateSandboxRequest represents a request to create a new sandbox.\n398: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n399:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n400:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n401:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n402: }\n403: \n404: // Validate rules:\n405: // - Kind must be AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n406: // - Namespace is required\n407: // - Name is required\n408: ```\n409: \n410: **`CreateSandboxResponse`**:\n411: \n412: ```go\n413: // CreateSandboxResponse represents the response after successful creation.\n414: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n415:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n416:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n417:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n418:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n419: }\n420: \n421: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n422:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // URL path prefix\n423:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n424:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n425: }\n426: ```\n427: \n428: ### Sandbox Creation Flow\n429: \n430: ```\n431: Client POST /v1/agent-runtime\n432:   вҶ’ authMiddleware (optional)\n433:     вҶ’ handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n434:       1. Parse and validate CreateSandboxRequest\n435:       2. Get AgentRuntime from Informer cache\n436:       3. Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim object (workload_builder)\n437:       4. StoreSandbox placeholder record\n438:       5. WatchSandboxOnce register one-time watcher\n439:       6. Create CR via dynamic client\n440:       7. Wait for SandboxReconciler notification (max 2 min)\n441:       8. Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n442:       9. UpdateSandbox with full info\n443:       10. Return CreateSandboxResponse\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ### Sandbox Object Building\n447: \n448: **AgentRuntime path** (`buildSandboxObject`):\n449: \n450: - Sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}` (8 random lowercase letters)\n451: - APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n452: - Kind: `Sandbox`\n453: - Labels: `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`, `managed-by`\n454: - Annotations: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n455: - Spec: `podTemplate` from `runtime.Spec.Template`, `replicas: 1`, `lifecycle.shutdownTime`\n456: \n457: **CodeInterpreter path**:\n458: \n459: - If `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create `SandboxClaim` instead of full Sandbox\n460: - If `AuthMode == picod`: Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n461: - Default ports: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if `spec.Ports` empty\n462: \n463: ### Pod IP Resolution\n464: \n465: ```go\n466: func resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n467:     // 1. Check sandbox annotation \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n468:     // 2. Try informer cache with podName\n469:     // 3. Fallback: list pods by label SandboxNameLabelKey\n470:     // 4. Select pod with OwnerReference to Sandbox\n471:     // 5. Return pod.Status.PodIP if running\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Error Handling and Rollback\n476: \n477: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Rollback Action |\n478: |------------|-------------|-----------------|\n479: | JSON binding failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n480: | Validation failure | 400 | None (before store) |\n481: | Template missing | 400 | None (before store) |\n482: | Not Found | 404 | None (before store) |\n483: | Auth failure | 401 | None (before handler) |\n484: | Timeout (>2 min) | 500 | Delete CR (30s timeout), Delete Store record |\n485: | Pod IP resolution failure | 500 | Delete CR, Delete Store record |\n486: | Store update failure | 500 | Log warning, CR cleaned by GC |\n487: \n488: ### Timeout Configuration\n489: \n490: | Operation | Timeout |\n491: |-----------|---------|\n492: | Wait for Sandbox running | 2 minutes |\n493: | CR deletion on rollback | 30 seconds |\n494: \n495: ## Impact Analysis\n496: \n497: ### Files created/modified\n498: \n499: | File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n500: |------|-------------|------|\n501: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | ~200 | Modified/Extended |\n502: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | ~300 | New |\n503: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | ~250 | New |\n504: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | ~150 | Modified/Extended |\n505: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ~50 | New |\n506: \n507: ### Downstream consumers\n508: \n509: | Consumer | Dependency |\n510: |----------|-----------|\n511: | WorkloadManager HTTP server | Uses handlers for sandbox endpoints |\n512: | client-go (AR-003) | Uses informers/listers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter lookup |\n513: | Store | Persists sandbox session information |\n514: | SandboxReconciler | Provides channel notification for running state |\n515: \n516: ### Breaking change risk\n517: \n518: - **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n519: - **Future**: Changes to request/response schema may impact clients\n520: - **Compatibility**: Follows existing patterns from AR-004 HTTP framework\n521: \n522: ## Alternatives Considered\n523: \n524: ### 1. Synchronous creation with long polling\n525: \n526: **Approach**: Block the HTTP request until Sandbox reaches running state.\n527: \n528: **Rejected because**: Synchronous creation would hold HTTP connections for up to 2 minutes, consuming server resources and potentially causing client timeouts. The async approach with Store placeholder allows immediate response with sessionId while background processing completes.\n529: \n530: ### 2. Use typed client instead of dynamic client for Sandbox CRD\n531: \n532: **Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs.\n533: \n534: **Rejected because**: Sandbox and SandboxClaim are external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`, not part of agentcube's API. Using `dynamic.Interface` + `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for operating on CRDs with unknown schemas, avoiding dependency on external type definitions.\n535: \n536: ### 3. Store session state in-memory only\n537: \n538: **Approach**: Keep sandbox session information only in memory.\n539: \n540: **Rejected because**: In-memory state would be lost on WorkloadManager restart. Using Redis/Store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling of WorkloadManager instances. Store also enables idempotency checks across instances.\n541: \n542: ### 4. Watch for Sandbox status after CR creation\n543: \n544: **Approach**: Create CR first, then register watcher.\n545: \n546: **Rejected because**: Race condition - Sandbox could reach running state before watcher registration completes, causing indefinite wait. The correct order is: register watcher first, then create CR.\n547: \n548: ### 5. Sequential integer sandbox IDs\n549: \n550: **Approach**: Use sequential integers (1, 2, 3...) for sandbox IDs instead of UUIDs.\n551: \n552: **Rejected because**: Sequential IDs require global coordination in distributed systems, creating a bottleneck. UUIDs provide global uniqueness without coordination, and align with Kubernetes naming conventions.\n553: \n554: ## Dependencies\n555: \n556: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n557: |------------|---------|---------|\n558: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n559: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | v0.34.1 | Dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs |\n560: | `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | UUID generation for sessionId |\n561: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | External | Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD definitions |\n562: | Store (Redis/Valkey) | - | Session persistence |\n563: \n564: ## Verification\n565: \n566: ```bash\n567: # Unit tests\n568: make test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n569: \n570: # Integration tests with fake clientset\n571: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run \"TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate\"\n572: \n573: # Build verification\n574: go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n575: \n576: # Verify handlers registered\n577: curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/v1/agent-runtime \\\n578:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n579:   -d '{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}'\n580: \n581: # Verify race conditions\n582: go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n583: ```\n584: \n585: ## References\n586: \n587: - [AR-003](#ar-003--crd-shared-types-and-constants) вҖ” client-go library for typed CRD access\n588: - [AR-004](#ar-004--http-service-framework) вҖ” HTTP server framework and routing\n589: - [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Generated client details\n590: - [sandbox-orchestration design](sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md) вҖ” Detailed technical design\n591: - [Kubernetes Dynamic Client](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/dynamic) вҖ” For external CRD operations\n592: \n593: ---\n594: \n595: *AR-005 вҖ” Module: pkg/workloadmanager вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 595 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Verify shared types can be imported and used\ngo vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-001](#ar-001--crd-agentruntime-type-definition) вҖ” AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [AR-002](#ar-002--crd-codeinterpreter-type-definition) вҖ” CodeInterpreter CRD types\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n---\n\n*AR-003 вҖ” Module: pkg/apis вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: S*\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775846060082,"end":1775846060098}}}}
